<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - INSTALL - OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>OUTPUT YOKE/COMPANION FLANGE</title>
        <para>You must remove the shifter housing in order to lock the transmission.</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Engage two (2) mainshaft sliding clutches into two (2) mainshaft gears to lock the
                transmission (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o6">Figure 246</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017o6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017o6" filename="../figg13/G13017o6.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 246. Output Yoke/Companion Flange</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the speedometer drive gear rotor or replacement spacer on the output shaft inside
                the rear bearing cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the slinger on the yoke is damaged, replace using a Slinger/Seal kit.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Slide the companion flange or yoke onto the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o7">Figure 247</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017o7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017o7" filename="../figg13/G13017o7.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 247. Companion Flange Onto Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the output shaft nut; tighten to 450 to 500 ft-lbs. (610 to 678 N&#8226;m) of torque
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13017o8">Figure 248</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13017o8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13017o8" filename="../figg13/G13017o8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 248. Install Output Shaft Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
